Friedrich Wilhelm KUEHN, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 11318. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit July 28, 1947. Rehearing Denied Aug. 25, 1947. Caspar A. Ornbaun and Everett H. Roan, both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. Frank J. Hennessy, U. S. Atty., and Edgar R. Bonsall, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before MATHEWS, BONE, and QRR, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On the grounds and for the reasons stated in its 'opinion (United States v. Holtz, D. C. N. D. Cal., 54 F.Supp. 63), the judgment of' the District Court is affirmed.
